<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/4999042-charlene-burke"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1605445553i/4999042._UY100_CR3,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/4999042-charlene-burke">Charlene Burke</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I discovered Octavia Butler first. In the fall of 2015 I was looking for examples of written Purpose Statements, as defined by Napoleon Hill in Law of<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I discovered Octavia Butler first. In the fall of 2015 I was looking for examples of written Purpose Statements, as defined by Napoleon Hill in Law of Success and Think and Grow Rich. I found hers, read it, then learned about her and her writings. Curious, I found the series on Amazon and purchased it. I read the series in a few days. <br /><br />I've read it twice and am now enjoying reading it a third time. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
