<div id="review_171284603" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/171284603" />
    <a title="Kirsten " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/833700-kirsten"><img alt="Kirsten " src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1607003371p2/833700.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/171284603?book_show_action=true">May 08, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kirsten " class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kirsten " href="/user/show/833700-kirsten">Kirsten </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/15769892-lilith-s-brood">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/833700-kirsten?shelf=kindle">kindle</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer171284603" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1309357305990595368"><b>
  <u>Dawn</u>
</b><br/><br/>Finally finished the first book in this trilogy. This is a very honest tale. She doesn&apos;t try to make humans better than they really are. There&apos;s no &quot;grateful just to be alive&quot; humans. These humans are angry, they are in denial, they are destructive. We are always told that humanity&apos;s greatest feature is its ability to adapt. Well, this situation proves that those that cannot adapt will not produce the next generation.<br/><br/>Ms Butler&apos;s books are works in the true sense of the word. They are not</span>
  <span id="freeText1309357305990595368" style="display:none"><b>
  <u>Dawn</u>
</b><br /><br />Finally finished the first book in this trilogy. This is a very honest tale. She doesn't try to make humans better than they really are. There's no "grateful just to be alive" humans. These humans are angry, they are in denial, they are destructive. We are always told that humanity's greatest feature is its ability to adapt. Well, this situation proves that those that cannot adapt will not produce the next generation.<br /><br />Ms Butler's books are works in the true sense of the word. They are not the type of sci-fi you read for the adventure or journey, they are the type that make you think.<br /><br /><b>
  <u>Adulthood Rites</u>
</b><br /><br />After finally finishing Dawn, Adulthood Rites went much faster. I think part of the problem with Dawn is it is a very cerebral novel with little action or dialogue. Adulthood Rites also lets you see how the family system and childhood growth in this unusual family actually will work in practice. We see one of the hybrid alien-human children growing and learning from his environment. We see how he interacts with his family and we also see him becoming an individual.<br /><br />I really liked this look at how things had changed on Earth and what problems were cropping up. It also really had me thinking of what the aliens call our hierarchical flaw. <br /><br /><b>
  <u>Imago</u>
</b><br /><br />This was probably the best of the trilogy. it focuses on another child. This one ends up becoming one of the other sexes. The one that isn't male or female. It is hard for me to imagine being this in-between sex, but the author did an excellent job. <br /><br />I also really liked the search for partners. It wants to stay on the planet. I am so glad I read this series. </span>
  <a data-text-id="1309357305990595368" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


